RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 68. Claiming Purse 13200. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WELDON G was lightly brushed at the start, moved forward under early coaxing, set the pace racing off the fence and facing outside pressure, was engaged more thoroughly coming past the midpoint of the turn, dueled while drifting out and under right-handed urging through the stretch and edged clear fending off that sparring partner. BLUESKIESANDANGELS got away alertly, settled in to press the pace from outside going three wide, drew nearly even past the five-sixteenths, put to urging past the quarter pole, dueled till late stretch while being carried out and was only second best. IRA CHAMP broke outwardly, stalked the leading pair four wide, was no match. HES BIG CHIEF broke a step slowly then was allowed to settle into stride at the back racing off the inside, moved out five wide and closer to the leaders coming to the five-sixteenths pole when put to urging, lacked the needed late kick. JEANO broke outwardly brushing a rival lightly, saved ground to no avail.

ENTRY.NAME: Jeano
ENTRY.COMMENT: brk out brush foe, saved ground, no menace

ENTRY.NAME: Weldon G
ENTRY.COMMENT: brushed brk, pace, inside-2path, duel, drifted out str, held foe

ENTRY.NAME: Hes Big Chief
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, settled, moved out 5w 5/16 & ask, no kick

ENTRY.NAME: Blueskiesandangels
ENTRY.COMMENT: away alertly, pressed, dueled 3wide, carried out, 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Ira Champ
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke outwardly, stalked pair, 4wide, no match

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 66. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MESSAGE DISCIPLINE moved forward inside a rival soon after the break to set the pace racing just off the rail, came out a bit in upper stretch, held rivals at bay. MAGNET AND STEEL broke a half-step slowly, moved up inside saving ground on the turn, came out a bit at the top of the stretch then back inside, attempted to rally inside the leader but could make no headway while securing the place over MASTER RED, who got away alertly but ceded the lead content to press from outside the eventual winner going three wide on the turn, could not match strides with that one and was outfinished for second. WHAT ABOUT JIMMY was encouraged at the break, chased five wide, went evenly. NORTHERN ORBIT broke a half-step slowly, moved up between runners going two to three wide into the turn, failed to rally. CRAFTY SWORD dropped back while lacking speed up the backstretch, saved ground on the turn, had no late kick. MR GYPSY pursued the leaders four wide, came up empty.

ENTRY.NAME: Magnet and Steel
ENTRY.COMMENT: 1/2 step slow, inside, sought room upper, no headway, got 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Northern Orbit
ENTRY.COMMENT: 1/2 step slow, 2-3w, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Message Discipline
ENTRY.OWNER: Flying B Ranch Cattle Company LLC
ENTRY.COMMENT: forward, pace, 2path, came out bit upper, held foes

ENTRY.NAME: Crafty Sword
ENTRY.COMMENT: outpaced, saved ground, no kick

ENTRY.NAME: Master Red
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed winner, 3wide, outfinished for 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Mr Gypsy
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4wide pursuit, empty

ENTRY.NAME: What About Jimmy
ENTRY.COMMENT: encouraged break, chased 5wide, evenly

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CAMANCHE RIVER attended the pace from outside going three to four wide on the turn, engaged for the lead turning for home, dueled outside and edged past a rival late under moderate urging. LUCKY MCCOY prompted the pace two to three wide between runners, took a narrow lead leaving the turn but was quickly challenged and overtaken by an outside rival, fought on dueling gamely inside that one but was outfinished. EASTER JIM stalked from outside the second flight three to four wide through the turn, kept on to secure show honors while no threat to the top pair. ST PATRICKS SWORD set a pressured pace inside but just off the rail, drifted out a bit in the stretch while weakening. CRYPTO MINER tracked inside the second flight, saved ground advancing some on the turn but could only run on evenly. SERVICEMAN chased two to three wide and between runners in the second flight, failed to rally. MR. SMOKEY lacked early speed and was outpaced.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 77. Allowance Purse 27600. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOSPEL BUZZ was reserved at the rear, advanced some along the inside on the far turn, came out four wide at the top of the stretch, took aim and drove past seventy yards from the wire under steady handling. EARS TO ME stalked from outside three to four wide, moved closer to take a narrow lead past the three-eighths, was clear by upper stretch but outkicked while second best. DOMINANT OKIE pressed three wide then moved closer early up the backstretch to force the issue, vied between runners on the far turn, kept on gamely under stout urging to fight for show honors over DENS DEVILLE, who got away well and quickly moved clear while shifting in, set the pace on or just off the rail but was soon overtaken, contended inside up the backstretch and on the far turn, was outkicked and lost the battle for third. PRINCE CAROLINA J rated in behind and between runners in the second flight early, fanned four wide turning for home, failed to rally. COUNTRY BRAVE was urged forward at the break but then forced to rate inside off heels early up the backstretch, pursued the leading pair into the far turn coming off the inside for that bend, dropped back and made no late bid.

ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved, inside 2nd turn, came out 4w upper, drove past 70yds

ENTRY.NAME: Dens Deville
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace, inside-2path, vied, outfinished for 3rd

ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed 3w, prompted pace, vied btw, fought for show

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG NORTHERN RIVER stalked off the leaders, moved out from three to five wide on the turn, struck the lead in upper stretch and cleared. RACE.FOOTNOTES: NOSTALGIA broke outwardly just a bit, attended the pace from outside, took a narrow lead past the seven-sixteenths, went three wide on the turn, kicked clear and was asked in mid-stretch, held safe. RACE.FOOTNOTES: GHOST HERO pressed from outside three wide, took command past the three-eighths, drifted nearer the rail turning into upper stretch once clear then back out, extended the margin while being kept to the task.
